info.description: Compete to hoard the most fish on a shared ice floe, cutting off your rival animals while the map shrinks!
info.ruleText:
Game setup:
1) Click 'Reset Game' to reshuffle all tiles, recall all player tokens, and reset all point totals back to zero
2) In turn order, place one token on the board at a time
* All starting tokens must be placed onto a tile with 1 fish on it
* For a 2-player game, use 4 tokens each
* For a 3-player game, use 3 tokens each
* For a 4-player game, use 2 tokens each

On your turn:
1) Move one of your tokens any distance in a straight line
* You cannot change directions during the move
* You cannot pass through any other tokens
* You cannot pass through any empty spots on the board
2) Pick up the tile you just left and add it to your player holder
3) If you cannot move any tokens, pick up all your tokens and the tiles they ended up on

Endgame:
* Endgame triggers when all players are out of legal moves
* At that point, the player with the most points wins the game
* If tied, then the player with the most number of tiles collected wins the game
